  • Package org.sensorhub.api.persistence

    • Class org.sensorhub.api.persistence.DataKey extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      4804063766602286733L

      • Serialized Fields

        • recordType

          java.lang.String recordType
          ID of record type (i.e. maps to a record structure definition).
          This field cannot be null.

        • timeStamp

          double timeStamp
          Time stamp of data record (e.g. measurement sampling time).
          If value is NaN, data record will never be selected when filtering on time stamp

        • producerID

          java.lang.String producerID
          ID of data producer (i.e. the entity that produced the data record).
          If value is null, data record will never be selected when filtering on producer ID

    • Class org.sensorhub.api.persistence.ObsKey extends DataKey implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      8685703972784653606L

      • Serialized Fields

        • foiID

          java.lang.String foiID
          ID of feature of interest (i.e. feature whose properties were observed/measured).
          If value is null, observation will never be selected when filtering on FoI ID

        • resultTime

          double resultTime
          Observation result time (i.e. time at which the observation result was obtained).
          If value is NaN, observation will never be selected when filtering on result time

        • samplingGeometry

          com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Polygon samplingGeometry
          Sampling Geometry (i.e. area or volume in 2D or 3D space, where the observation was made).
          If value is null, FoI geometry is used instead when provided. If neither geometry is provided, observation will never be selected when filtering on geometry.
          In a given data store, all geometries must be expressed in the same coordinate reference system.
